Once upon a time, Alan Cox <alan@lxorguk.ukuu.org.uk> said:
>No power off on shutdown is not SMP safe. It kind of happens to work on a lot
>of boards. If making that APM call reformats your disk and plays tetris
>on an SMP box the bios vendor is within spec (if a little peculiar).
So if I use a drive I can do without (or just boot of CD without a hard
drive) and try to power off on shutdown on an SMP machine, I might get
to play Tetris?  Cool - where can I get one of these? :-)
